caption: Pretty park not far from the train station. The park has two playgrounds for children. Really well kept and tidy. Even has a community garden here which is nice to walk around.
It looked like a great place to spend a summer day with family or friends.

Nice park to have a small nap under smiths sun . The park is clean , no trace of insect nor dog waste . I took a nap here for 20 minutes after having my lunch in a restaurant nearby . It is a good park to hang out with your friends or dog . There are plenty of restaurant nearby as well

Amazing garden, not appreciated enough. The location is spectacular: just 5m walk from the station which makes it a perfect break spot. No matter if you want to chill in the sun with group of friends or vomit after travel it always serves well. Perfect balance of florals and green makes it even more pleasant.  üëâüèºüëâüèºTourist hack (especially during the Olympics): perfect spot if you can‚Äôt find toilet on the station or the line is too long while emergency. Beautiful park, not a tourist place but in between residential place, proper swings & other for children, everywhere benches for sitting. Loved to see a small hut which had balcony & window  , full of flower pots, a well for water in front of this hut. Overall a lovely garden.

Nice park, plenty of bins. Short walk from the train station. Lots of flower beds. Big section of children's play areas. There is also some spray machines which spray out water which is very nice on a hot day. Toilets on site.
This garden space features a large children‚Äôs playground, many trees and flowers, boule site, and features a former  site of a convent and hospital..very close to the Canal area..

This is a cute little parc with trees and a playground for kids. My wife who is Persian had heard that it was being renamed for Mahsa Amini, the Iranian girl whose death at the hands of the morality police triggered the zan, zendegi, azadi protests around the world. We saw no evidence of the name change on site but the declaration was fairly recent.

We took a whisk going to this park. Lovely starting 30 minutes, only to be interrupted by a cacophony of un-muffled wind instruments. We would suggest, in the future, pour la tranquillit√© de tous, that sponges be placed in the pipes of said instruments.  Mais bon, c‚Äôest Paris.
Very nice park, big playground for kids. I enjoyed it a lot.
A nice garden set back from the street which gives a view on the canal Saint Martin. A bandstand. The children's play park is fantastic. The grass is original because it forms waves.
For anyone that needs to cry in a park like I did after an ironically magnificent rejection from a Parisian yoga class, this park offers comfort.
Nice and cosy park
Such a nice place for morning walk and child recreation corner is well equipped. But no security arranged on site.
It's spring break in parts of Paris, so there were lots of kids having fun .

Great park. There are 2 playground areas as well as space to relax alone or with friends.  Only issue, the toilets were locked. I'm not sure if it was because of the holiday (Bastille Day). I was lucky the local restaurants were kind and allowed use of their facilities.

Beautiful location to chill at during a hot day. The garden section is full of interesting plants, the relaxation area has plenty of places to sit, as well as these really great water misting tower things that most water Avary once in a while. A great place to eat your lunch
Cute small park, kids playing, people jogging. Went there to wait for a train. My experience was relaxing and quiet. Birds were chirping and the cars from the street weren't really audible.

My teeth started falling out, when I called to get the brand to get them fixed elsewhere he ignored my calls on his cell phone and when calling the establishment he avoided my calls as well as I waited on the phones for hours just to know the BRAND I had to tell my new dentist. I wast 5000 euros in a small apartment above a pizza place with dust everywhere, every single time in sever pain, only to be talked down to when crying. My dentist today is telling me to sew him for not answering and giving me the "passport" of my teeth. Do not go,  you will just be wasting money for him to cause you great, excruciatierng pain. The times I have come out of that "apartment" and had to go back home by metro and RER, on hour and half ride- crying on the floor of the metro in pain. Many other lies that I could have avoided I have learned from my new dentist today but unfortunately trusted and wasted my money on this SCAM.
Beautiful set up but toilets were locked, which seems like a big issue!

A pleasant place with small biodiversity areas and lots of interesting corners, including beehives. There's a bandstand, too!
Beautiful, little but well looked after park with lots of nice planting and benches. Today I enjoyed the beautiful flowers in the community garden area.

Went here at 8pm for an evening picnic. Lots of families and couples still in the park, and people boxing in the pegoda. It was very chilled out and a great, safe, outdoor space to get some evening air.

A nice park to spend some leisure time. Not pretentious and very well made, it good for children's as well as getting tanned on the grass or hanging out, drinking a beer with some friends. Open 24/24 in summer!
This garden features some playgrounds, a gazebo if you need to hide from the rain and some toilets as well. It offers many benches to sit around and you can visit with your dog as well.
A very nice park and potentially a good place for children to play. However, it doesn't feel safe, a lot of dodgy men gathering around some dirty booth next to the basketball pitch
Small but nice park with lovely garden tendet by the locals. There are many children so it's not quiet but still good to spend time to rest. There is a playground.
Right place to visit if you want to experience how local people chill
Beautiful, clean, family park. Grass is au naturel, uncut. This part of Canal St Martin is posh & scenic (not all canal paths are created equal!)
Great place to relax near the train stations. I saw a lot of weary travelers snoozing with their luggage. There is also a free toilet and drinking water.

Simply beautiful! One park that leaves you light weighted and well energised everytime for a visit. Blooming life everywhere you go during all seasons around!  One place you MUST visit if you're searching for a park close to everything like metros, shops, cosmetic boutiques, food markets and much more! R√©publique is one metro station very close to the park - brown line 11 that takes you into town in minutes!
Beautiful secluded park with teensy rolling hills, plenty of playground stuff for baby + toddlers + some as-to-go-unamed adult...also tons of benches. Really just perfect for all sizes and ages!
As all the gardens in Europe and obviously in France are all beautiful some are more gorgeous than others but are in their class Of Their Own still gorgeous

Best kids park there for 2 to 7 year olds
A colourful neighborhood park in the 10`arr.
Really great play area aimed at very young kids. Plenty of space to play and lots of benches where parents and nannies sit while the kids go wild
